Rusal Forecasts 2011 Aluminum Price at $2,600 to $2,800

-- B y   J a s m i n e   W a n g
-- 
2011-06-23T08:51:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/rusal-sees-2011-aluminum-prices-at-2-600-to-2-800-correct-.html
United Co. Rusal, the world’s
largest aluminum producer, said prices will average between
$2,600 and $2,800 a metric ton this year.  Rusal’s First Deputy Chief Executive Vladislav Soloviev
announced the prices to reporters in  Hong Kong  today.  The price for three-month delivery has averaged $2,575 a
ton this year and was $2,531 today at 4:48 p.m. Hong Kong time
on the London Metal exchange. Prices may rise to as much as
$3,000 in 2012, Steve Hodgson, Rusal’s head of marketing said on
June 14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jasmine Wang in Hong Kong at 
 jwang513@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Hobbs at 
 ahobbs4@bloomberg.net  